Package com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.platform.client.tcp

Contains TCP implementation of the Client interface.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TcpChannelInitializer
    Performs initialization of new SocketChannels created by TcpSequentialClient.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    TcpMessage<Message,Response>
    Represents message that TcpSequentialClient is able to send.
    TcpResponse<Response>
    Represents response that TcpSequentialClient returns.
    TcpSequentialClient<Message,Response>
    A TCP implementation of the Client interface that is suitable only to access TCP servers that don't shuffle responses and can tolerate reuse of TCP connections by a client.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    TcpSequentialClientAddress
    Required for injection into a TcpSequentialClient.
    TcpSequentialClientConnectTimeout
    Required for injection into a TcpSequentialClient.
    TcpSequentialClientName
    Required for injection into a TcpSequentialClient.
    TcpSequentialClientThreadFactory
    Required for injection into a TcpSequentialClient.
    TcpSequentialClientWorker
    Required for injection into a TcpSequentialClient.
